===Adjective===
{{en-adj|angr|ier}}

# Displaying or feeling [[anger]].
#: ''His face became '''angry'''.''
#: ''An '''angry''' mob started looting the warehouse.''
# {{context|said about a wound or a rash}} Inflamed and [[painful]].
#: ''The broken glass left two '''angry''' cuts across my arm.''
# {{figuratively|said about the sky or the sea}} Dark and stormy, [[menacing]].
#: '''''Angry''' clouds raced across the sky.''
#* {{quote-book|1756|[[w:Christopher Smart|Christopher Smart]]|3=[http://books.google.com/books?id=fnpYmCFiZlcC The Book of the Epodes]|chapter=Ode II|by=[[w:Horace|Horace]]
